1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 c5 5. g3 {A late attempt to transpose to the Catalan territory. This may be completely playable against any other response by Black on the 4th move. But here, we are ready to smash White's centre.} cxd4 6. Nxd4 e5 {Snatching the first opportunity to grab space in the centre. Gaining space in the centre with a tempo is a cherry on the cake.} 7. Nf3 d4 {And we march ahead, this time attacking White's other Knight. I am sure White must be regretting bringing his Knights early on in the game.} 8. Na4 (8. Nb5 $2 {is simply met by} a6 9. Na3 Nc6 {Black enjoys more or less a winning advantage thanks to our central control. We are also looking forward to pushing further with ... e4 .}) 8... Nc6 {Defending not only the e5 -Pawn but also the d4 -Pawn so that we can play ... e4 next and gain more space.} 9. Bg2 e4 10. Nd2 Bf5 {Black enjoys a nice golden centre, which is difficult to achieve even with the white Pieces.} *

