he move in Agulnick, M (2033)-Cravens, D (2125) IECC email 2012, which ended in 0-1 in 62 moves.}) 14. Nd2 ({The alternative is the endgame} 14. Qd2 $6 Qxd2+ 15. Nxd2 O-O-O {, followed by moves like ... Rg8 and ... e4 . Black is dominating in this position.}) 14... O-O-O {Black's King is safe on the Queenside, but the same cannot be said about White's King after O-O . We can continue with ... e4 next with complete dominance in the centre.} *

