lso be transferred to the Kingside if required in the attack.} 12. Rc1 {This allows Black to simply equalise.} Nxd4 13. Qxd4 Be5 {Preparing to break with ... d4 next.} 14. Qd2 (14. Qd3 {leads to the same thing after} d4 $1 15. exd4 Qxd4 16. Qxd4 Bxd4 {transposing.}) 14... d4 {A typical central break that eliminates the weak isolated d -Pawn.} 15. exd4 Qxd4 16. Qxd4 Bxd4 17. Bf3 Rb8 {Black guards the b7 -Pawn freeing our light-squared Bishop to develop on the next move. The dust has settled. We have few Pieces remaining on the board and this endgame is heading towards a draw.} *

