becomes shaky.} 12. Qxd2 O-O-O {We take our King away from the centre while placing our Rook opposite to White's Queen at the same time.} 13. e3 {This is the most logical move in this position, but it allows Black's Pieces to jump into action with threats.} Bf5 {Black not only hits the Queen but also carries threats like ... Nb4 .} 14. Qc1 Nb4 {This wins for Black.} *

