becomes shaky.} 12. Qxd2 Rd8 {This is also a possibility for Black. Apart from indirectly targeting White's Queen, the d7 -Bishop is supported, which will help us to play ... O-O in the near future.} 13. e3 Bf5 {Placing the Bishop actively on f5 before White gets to play Qc2 .} (13... g6 {was GM Ju Wenjun's choice, and Black got compensation there as well. But Bf5 is better. Nyzhnyk, I (2622)-Ju, W (2559) Chicago 2016 ended in a draw in 82 moves.}) 14. Qc1 g6 {Only now, preparing the fianchetto of the dark-squared Bishop and then going for ... O-O .} 15. Be2 Bg7 16. O-O O-O {It is quite evident that all of Black's Pieces are active and putting pressure on White's position. At some point, we will regain our lost Pawn. Black enjoys a pleasant compensation thanks to our active Pieces.} *

