1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 c5 5. cxd5 cxd4 6. Qxd4 exd5 7. Qa4+ {This would be a bit too prophylactic! Black starts chasing away White's Queen.} Bd7 8. Qb3 {Feels like a nice move, creating a double attack on Black's Pawns, but we hardly care about any of them. We value initiative more in this position since White has been wasting a lot of moves with his Queen.} Nc6 9. Nxd5 (9. Qxb7 $4 {is a blunder due to} Rb8 10. Qa6 Nb4 {we are about to win decisive material.}) 9... Be6 {Forcing White to exchange on f6 .} 10. Nxf6+ Qxf6 {Once again, White's Queen finds itself under attack. Their Queen must be used to it by now.} 11. Qxb7 {Now Black snatches a crushing initiative:} Bb4+ {A strong check that disturbs White's Piece coordination.} 12. Nd2 Rc8 {This is also winning for Black.} *

