r b8 -Knight.} 15. Ng4+ (15. Bb5 {is also met by} Nc6 {when} 16. Bxc6 bxc6 17. Ng4+ Kg6 {transposes.}) 15... Kg6 ({Not} 15... Ke7 $6 {due to} 16. Rb5 $1 {hitting the bishop and the b7 -Pawn, and White snatches the initiative.}) 16. Bb5 {White develops the Bishop actively and prepares to exchange it for our Knight.} Nc6 {We could not care less. Our priority is to bring out Pieces our quickly.} 17. Bxc6 bxc6 18. Rd4 {Finally, White is all set to regain the Pawn.} a5 {A simple reply.} 19. Rxe4 Rhe8 {Black is doing completely fine in this endgame.} *

