eatens to ruin our Pawn structure with Bxc6 .} Nb4 {Of course, we prevent White's idea and further activate our Knight at the same time. Our b4 -Knight can come back to d5 if needed to solidify the position.} 15. Bd4 a6 {Kicking the Bishop from its active post.} 16. Be2 Nbd5 {Our Knight is beautifully placed on the central d5 -square. We also get an option of exchanging White's c3 -Knight, releasing the pressure off the e4 -Pawn.} *

